Just announced: Google Cloud Next sessions 

The session library for Google Cloud Next is now live! Join us at San Francisco’s Moscone Center, August 29–31, to experience new AI-powered developer tools, find out how to balance speed with security, and explore how Google is making it much easier to build apps.

 

 

250+ sessions to explore

Here are a few sessions we recommend for application developers:
[ Image ]

 
 
 
 
[ Image ]

Move ahead

Increase your productivity and potential with Duet AI for developers

Learn

Ten best practices for modern app development

Perform

Performance optimizations for Java applications
 

Be sure to attend our spotlight session, What’s next for application developers, to learn how we’re transforming the developer experience with AI. 
 
[ Image ]

Use code NEXT1199_CTLG to register for only $1,199 USD*

 
Register now
Register now [[https://cloud.withgoogle.com/next?code=NEXT1199_CTLG&utm_source=cloud_sfdc&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=FY23-Q3-global-ENDM33-physicalevent-er-next-2023-mc&utm_content=next23_noram_invite8_app_dev&utm_term=-]]

 

Get access to Innovators Plus at no additional cost when you register for Next ’23 with your Google Developer Profile. Enjoy a year of Google Cloud on-demand training, Google Cloud credits, a certification exam voucher, and more.**

* The $1,199 USD price is only valid with code NEXT1199_CTLG through 11:59 PM PT on June 30, 2023, or until sold out. This code is nontransferable.

 

** Benefit redemption is subject to limitations. If you’re eligible for this offer, you will receive an email within 48 business hours after registering for Next ’23 inviting you to activate your subscription at no charge. You must activate your subscription no later than 30 days after Next ’23 concludes. For customers in the European Economic Area, the UK, and Switzerland, Innovators Plus is restricted to business or professional use. Read the full terms and conditions.

 

We sent you this email because you have indicated that you are willing to receive periodic emails on news, product updates, and invitations to events from the Google Cloud team.


If you no longer want to receive these Google Cloud emails, unsubscribe or customize your communication preferences.


If you no longer want to receive emails about Google Cloud Next but still want to receive periodic emails from the Google Cloud team, opt out from Next ’23 instead.
